        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="business">H. Evans &amp; Bro.<lb/>Wholesale Dealers
                        in<lb/>Tobacco, Cigars, Snuffs, Papers, &amp;c.</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <address><addrLine>No. 102 1/2 Main Street,</addrLine><addrLine> One Door North of the Taylor Hotel,</addrLine>
        <addrLine><name type="place">Winchester, Va.</name></addrLine></address>
                        <date value="1868-10-03">October 3 1868</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Bro,</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>After I Wrote the letter on Yesterday I have Come to the Conclusion that We had
                    better not start business in Staunton as John is opposed to us and Will do all
                    he can against us= if he was favorable to us We Could do better= I think it is
                    selfish in him I will not think as Much of him <orig reg="hereafter">hear
                    after</orig>= let us try some other Point= I would give the room up if I was
                    You= but if you want to go in I will put half the <orig reg="money">Mony</orig>
                    in and I will Keep My situation and if it pays I will then come to Staunton=
                    Write Me What you think <orig reg="of it">ofit</orig>= them <orig
                        reg="factories">Factrys</orig> will be a big Drawback to Our Business up
                    there</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Truly</salute>
                    <signed>Wm L Evans</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript"><pb n="2"/>We can Wait <orig reg="until">untill</orig>
                        spring= and then perhaps We Will do better<lb/>Truly<lb/>Wm L Evans</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
